# SUPERSEDES the prior five-file scenario (@scenario_hash:f7af63457d95962f) under
# ADR-043 D2 (lead-y9e2; reconciling the lead mirror with the BC growth landed via
# lead-ow4d/lead-0act, BC scenario 211 @0a3a8267109b5792). The single rendered,
# shell-sourceable ops-coordinates artifact "bin/ops-coordinates" (ADR-043 D2
# FINALIZED) is a NEW shop-owned ops file written by "shop-templates bootstrap"
# alongside the other ops scaffolding, so the enumeration GROWS from five to six
# files: "bin/ops-coordinates" is added to the positive enumeration and to the
# no-".claude/"-placement exclusion. The producer behavior is pinned by scenario
# 211 (@0a3a8267109b5792); the consumers that source it are 204
# (@b7ea0de32ef49854) and 205 (@1885dea2b4550fde). This is the lead-side mirror of
# an already-landed BC enumeration growth; the BC re-superseded its converged_ops
# exclusivity (b764caa1dea99fcb -> 0a7e4c29fc7db52b) in lockstep with 211.
#
# bin/footing is DELIBERATELY NOT in this set. Although "shop-templates bootstrap"
# renders "bin/footing" (scenario 187, @b05fff82d0d10f4a, lead-y4pg), footing is a
# transient ONE-TIME bootstrap orchestrator (rendered, run once to reach footing,
# pinned by scenario 184), not persistent shop-owned ops scaffolding that "update"
# advises-on-drift (139/140/141). The BC's landed converged_ops re-supersede keeps
# footing OUTSIDE _LEAD_OPS_FILES; this lead mirror matches that, so footing is not
# enumerated here. (Earlier prose in scenario 187 flagged a footing-growth of 174;
# that flag is superseded by the ops-coordinates growth and the footing-outside
# decision recorded here.)
#
# Earlier history: the prior five-file scenario itself SUPERSEDED a six-file
# scenario (@scenario_hash:cb1e585684ff4a14) under PDR-020 slice 2 (lead-6ox4),
# which retired "Dockerfile.<slug>-shell" and the dedicated shell image; per the
# PDR-020 launcher/leaf split "bin/shop-shell" launches an ephemeral bc-lead
# LAUNCHER image (carrying the docker CLI) which stands up the leaf-BC session on
# bc-base. The no-".claude/"-placement coverage and the positive absence of any
# rendered "Dockerfile.<slug>-shell" are PRESERVED here.
@scenario_hash:7be5c3b0b319eb56
Scenario Outline: the ops scaffolding file-set written by bootstrap for a "lead" shop named "<slug>" enumerates exactly six shop-owned files additively — "compose.yaml", "bin/shop-shell", "bin/shop-scenario-completion", "bin/agent-vault-provision", "bin/agent-vault-check", and "bin/ops-coordinates" — each at a shop-owned path outside any ".claude/" subdirectory, and writes NO dedicated shell Dockerfile, because per PDR-020 the shell image is retired and "bin/shop-shell" launches an ephemeral bc-lead launcher (which stands up the leaf-BC on bc-base) instead
  Given an existing git repository at a target directory "/tmp/example-lead-shop"
  When I invoke the "shop-templates" bootstrap entry point with shop type "lead", shop name "<slug>", and target directory "/tmp/example-lead-shop"
  Then the exit code is 0
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a top-level file named "compose.yaml" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a file at "bin/shop-shell" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a file at "bin/shop-scenario-completion" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a file at "bin/agent-vault-provision" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a file at "bin/agent-vault-check" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains a file at "bin/ops-coordinates" not under any ".claude/" subdirectory
  And after the invocation the target directory contains no top-level file named "Dockerfile.<slug>-shell"
  And after the invocation the target directory contains no top-level file named "Dockerfile.shopsystem-shell"
  And the directory at "/tmp/example-lead-shop/.claude/canonical/" does not contain a file named "compose.yaml", "shop-shell", "shop-scenario-completion", "agent-vault-provision", "agent-vault-check", or "ops-coordinates"

  Examples:
    | slug       |
    | shopsystem |
    | dummyco    |
